cs.HC, cs.SE, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on providing a recommendation system to help users and developers manage the resources available on mobile devices. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper proposes a solution to a software engineering problem related to app performance optimization. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of metrics and optimization techniques to generate optimal sets of apps. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) could be relevant as the paper deals with app marketplaces and the social aspect of users relying on recommendations to make decisions. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could also be relevant as the paper proposes a solution that involves solving an optimization problem.
